Judul: 1ST ASIA OCEANIA GEOSCIENCES  SEMINARS, JULY 5-9, 2004. SINGAPORE
Abstrak:
The IASSHA 2001 and 2003 marine surveys successfully identified submarine  
hydrothermal and volcanic activity at western side of Sangihe arc and oceanic  
island on eastern margin of Celebes Sea Plate, Northern Sulawesi, Indonesia. The  
Sangihe arc, in NS direction is a product of westward subduction of Molucca Sea  
Plate (MSP) beneath the Celebes Sea Plate since Late Miocene
Kata Kunci: ocenia geoscience Seminars; westward subducted lithospheric; Molucca Sea Plate,
